While only slightly related as this is also occurring with Hibernate 5 in JBoss EAP 7.0 with a JTA Data Source connecting to MS SQLServerExpress - Red Hat says this didnt occur in JBoss 4, only JBoss 6 and up.  You probably cant view the full solution unless you have a red hat support account but [here][1] is the link. The problem and solutions labeled as &quot;Transaction cannot proceed STATUS_COMMITTED&quot; during commit in EAP 6 and later&quot;

I do get the exception on every attempted commit with the commit failing.  Red hat basically says &quot;Use an interposed synchronization registered when the connection is first obtained to clean up connection context as required&quot;

They say the root cause is &quot;Using a data source connection during the afterCompletion phase of the transaction lifecycle is not supported in EAP 6&quot;

They also refer to this [discussion][2] by Iron Jacamar regarding valid use of connections with regard to transaction boundaries.

They provide custom code supplied as an implementation of [org.hibernate.connection.ConnectionProvider][3] and say see also the hibernate.connection.provider_class property defintion in [Table 3.4. Hibernate JDBC and Connection Properties][4]

Hopefully this might help someone else regardless of if they&#39;re using EclipseLink or Hibernate.

